content:
Hello, I am an 5-th year undergraduate Computing Science student that will be graduating with a Bachelors in Honors Computing Science in Fall 2021.
I’ve worked in both private and academic research institutions during my undergraduate program from developing a ML-guided performance prediction model for LLVM-IR, to developing a real-time occupancy flow and recognition algorithm for a low resolution infrared camera.
In addition to my experience above. I worked as a teaching assistant for a year for an introductory computing course for computer science and engineering students teaching introductory programming and algorithms in Python and C++. I was also a teaching assistant for an operating system course for one semester.
